race.comment: MOSQUITO AWARD (10) debuted off promising jumpouts beaten a whisker at Yarra Valley as favourite. Rode the speed and with the extra fitness this is a winnable assignment. BUTTERCUP (8) is a danger presenting off narrow defeats at Terang and Warrnambool the latest. Maps for the run of the race and the in-form Meech is a positive jockey engagement. RED FALCON (6) resumes for a metro yard and went well three back on debut. Didn't have the best of it on wet tracks following and he's been fitted with two jumpouts. Keep safe. KIJIVU (4) has the ability and will be better for his first-up run at Warrnambool when he was slow away. Look for him to be hitting the line. POPTHEBUBBLY (12) resumes and won a recent Terang jumpout. Both starts have been on the turf and a market watch is advised.
